  "text": "As was shown before, positions of chromatin domains may reflect distribution of certain histone modifications and correlate with gene expression [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Thus, we separately analyzed localization of genes with high and low expression levels in CEF ( Figure 3D -F and Supplementary Figure  S6) . We found that both categories of genes were enriched in domain borders, but for actively expressed genes, the enrichment was much more prominent. Clustering of actively expressed genes near domain borders in CEF is even more evident from expression intensity plots, presented on Figure  3D .",
